Here's tonight's challenge: Write a letter to a celebrity (rock star, politician, athlete, movie star, etc.) convincing them you should become best friends.

Challenge accepted. Does anyone know this guy's address?

Dear Bill Murray,

This might sound kind of straight forward, but will you be my best friend?

Hear me out, I'm sure you get a ton of people asking you that question several times a day, but just ignore them. You see, we're both from the suburbs of Chicago so I think that's reason enough. No?

Well, I'm a huge fan of your movies and I can recite so many of your lines. So, so many!

We could watch a movie like, <em>Ghostbusters</em> or <em>Tootsie</em> or <em>Rushmore</em> and I'll say what you're going to say even before you say it. Wouldn't that be cool?

<a href="http://www.chicagonow.com/new-abides/files/2015/10/back_off_scientist_ghostbusters.gif"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-4496" alt="back_off_scientist_ghostbusters" src="http://www.chicagonow.com/new-abides/files/2015/10/back_off_scientist_ghostbusters.gif" width="500" height="333" /></a>

I still haven't sold you yet? Well, I also like to quote your characters at random times during the day.

I can't stop saying, "How interesting. How bizarre," from one of my favorite movies, <em>The Royal Tenenbaums</em>. I can't even hear <em>Star Wars</em> without singing it in a lounge singer's voice. "Star Wars, nothing but Star Wars."

<a href="http://www.chicagonow.com/new-abides/files/2015/10/tootsie.gif"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-4497" alt="tootsie" src="http://www.chicagonow.com/new-abides/files/2015/10/tootsie.gif" width="348" height="216" /></a>

Even though I join half the world population in loving your movies, you just seem like a cool guy. I'm always reading about your showing up at random birthday parties, crashing engagement photos and singing karaoke.

So, I just want to throw it out there. If you're ever back in your hometown and you're looking for a new best friend, I'm your gal.

