Here's how you do it:

<strong>Ingredients:</strong>

<strong>1/2 cup peanut butter (or any nut butter)</strong>

<strong>2 tbsp coconut oil</strong>

<strong>2 tbsp maple syrup or honey (non-vegan option)</strong>

<strong>1/4 tsp vanilla extract </strong>

1. Add peanut butter to a medium sized bowl.

<a href="http://www.chicagonow.com/new-abides/files/2015/09/1-DSC_0001.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-4422" alt="1-DSC_0001" src="http://www.chicagonow.com/new-abides/files/2015/09/1-DSC_0001.jpg" width="800" height="534" /></a>

2. Add coconut oil.

<a href="http://www.chicagonow.com/new-abides/files/2015/09/1-DSC_0003.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-4435" alt="1-DSC_0003" src="http://www.chicagonow.com/new-abides/files/2015/09/1-DSC_0003.jpg" width="800" height="646" /></a>

3. Add honey or maple syrup. (I used maple syrup.)

<a href="http://www.chicagonow.com/new-abides/files/2015/09/3-DSC_0005.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-4424" alt="3-DSC_0005" src="http://www.chicagonow.com/new-abides/files/2015/09/3-DSC_0005.jpg" width="800" height="534" /></a>

4. Add vanilla extract.

<a href="http://www.chicagonow.com/new-abides/files/2015/09/1-DSC_0010.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-4429" alt="1-DSC_0010" src="http://www.chicagonow.com/new-abides/files/2015/09/1-DSC_0010.jpg" width="800" height="534" /></a>

5. Mix ingredients well.

<a href="http://www.chicagonow.com/new-abides/files/2015/09/4-DSC_0015.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-4425" alt="4-DSC_0015" src="http://www.chicagonow.com/new-abides/files/2015/09/4-DSC_0015.jpg" width="800" height="696" /></a>

6. Line a container with parchment paper or plastic wrap and pour in the mixture. I used a bread pan and parchment paper, but really any medium sized container will work.

<a href="http://www.chicagonow.com/new-abides/files/2015/09/5-DSC_0019.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-4426" alt="5-DSC_0019" src="http://www.chicagonow.com/new-abides/files/2015/09/5-DSC_0019.jpg" width="800" height="534" /></a>

7. Pop into the freezer and let it set for about 45 minutes to an hour. When ready, remove from the liner, and cut into pieces. This makes about eight servings.

<a href="http://www.chicagonow.com/new-abides/files/2015/09/1-DSC_0023.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-4436" alt="1-DSC_0023" src="http://www.chicagonow.com/new-abides/files/2015/09/1-DSC_0023.jpg" width="800" height="485" /></a>

This fudge will get all gooey if left out, so it's best served cold, right out of the freezer.

Enjoy!

