I've decided I'm going to get back on the horse and start blogging again. Why? Because I love writing this blog and interacting with my readers is just plain fun and awesome. I'm very eloquent as you can see, but it's true.

<a href="http://www.chicagonow.com/new-abides/files/2015/09/1-Twinkle-and-Flower-Party.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-4390" alt="1-Twinkle and Flower Party" src="http://www.chicagonow.com/new-abides/files/2015/09/1-Twinkle-and-Flower-Party.jpg" width="800" height="441" /></a>

I'm revamping my blog so it's not going to be about doing something new every day or really following any sort of theme. It will still be me and I'll be writing about all sorts of topics.

I have a lot of ideas running through my head at all times. Sometimes I jot down little notes about stuff I want to write about. Then I forget and I find a piece of scrap paper that says "zombie apocalypse food" or "my house smells." You know, things that that the public finds interesting and demands to know more about.

I also enjoy an inner monologue that causes me to laugh out loud, seemingly at the wall. Am I normal? Are you guys the same way? Do you also question food options during the zombie apocalypse?

Let me know as you join me on this new path of writing that I've never tried before. Writing about nothing, something and everything in between.

Also...new post later today!

Hope to see you there,

Christine

